  "doc_id": "17454",
  "text": "When supplied by a square-wave VSI [CITATION_1] , the DTP induction machine draws large current harmonics of the order k = 6 · n ± 1, (n = 1, 3, 5, . . .), which do not contribute to the air-gap flux and do not influence the torque pulsations. These harmonics (5th, 7th, . . .) are mapped in the machine (µ 1 , µ 2 ) subspace (being thus limited only by the stator resistance and the stator leakage inductance) and drastically reduce machine efficiency [CITATION_2] .",
